http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Create-awareness-on-government-schemes%E2%80%99/article13979943.ece

Maneka Gandhi, Union Minister for Women and Child Development, has underlined the need for the party workers and leaders to strive hard to ensure that the benefits of the welfare schemes of the National Democratic Alliance (NDA) government reached the people. Addressing party workers here on Sunday, Ms. Gandhi dwelt at length on the various welfare schemes announced by the government and also the development works being taken up in the district. She said, “It is the duty of the party workers to create awareness among the people about the achievements of the Union government.”She also said that the union government had sanctioned Rs. 30 crores and Rs. 80 crores under AMRIT Scheme for Hosapete and Ballari, respectively, besides promising to develop Daroji Railway Station as a model station adjacent to the Daroji Sloth Bear sanctuary.B. Sriramulu, MP, spoke about the development works proposed for the district, including improving the NH 63 between Ballari and Gooty.B.S. Anand Singh, Vijayanagar MLA, was present.Ms. Gandhi visited an anganwadi and interacted with the children and teachers.